00:34.920 --> 00:37.229
AMANDA: Good morning, Mr Blake.
My name's Amanda.

00:37.520 --> 00:39.476
I've got a couple of questions
here for you today

00:39.640 --> 00:43.110
to establish your eligibility for
Employment Support Allowance.

00:43.480 --> 00:45.471
It won't take up much of your time.

00:46.760 --> 00:48.273
Could I just ask firstly,

00:48.440 --> 00:51.989
can you walk more than 50 metres
unassisted by any other person?

00:52.320 --> 00:53.833
DAN: Yes.
AMANDA: Okay.

00:54.040 --> 00:57.999
Can you raise either arm as if to
put something in your top pocket?

00:58.120 --> 01:00.998
DAN: I've filled this in already
on your 52-page form.

01:01.000 --> 01:02.558
AMANDA: Yeah, I can see that you have

01:02.680 --> 01:06.036
but, unfortunately, I couldn't
make out what you had said there.

01:07.160 --> 01:08.513
DAN: Yes.

01:10.560 --> 01:13.028
AMANDA: Can you raise either arm
to the top of your head

01:13.040 --> 01:15.031
as if you are putting on a hat?

01:15.040 --> 01:17.416
DAN: I've telt you, there's nowt wrong
with me arms and legs.

01:17.440 --> 01:19.456
AMANDA: Could you just answer
the question, please.

01:19.480 --> 01:20.856
DAN: Well, you've got me
medical records.

01:20.880 --> 01:22.438
Can we just talk about me heart?

01:22.960 --> 01:25.474
AMANDA: D'you think you could
just answer these questions?

01:25.600 --> 01:27.033
DAN: Okay.

01:27.320 --> 01:30.437
AMANDA: So was that a yes, that you
can put a hat on your head?

01:30.560 --> 01:33.279
DAN: Yes.
AMANDA: Okay, that's great.

01:35.960 --> 01:38.952
AMANDA: Can you press a button
such as a telephone keypad?

01:40.000 --> 01:41.736
DAN: There's nowt wrong
with me fingers either.

01:41.760 --> 01:44.194
I mean, we're getting farther
and farther away from me heart.

01:44.320 --> 01:47.118
AMANDA: If we could just keep
to these questions, thank you.

01:47.480 --> 01:49.391
Do you have any significant difficulty

01:49.520 --> 01:52.080
conveying a simple message to strangers?

01:52.200 --> 01:56.079
DAN: Yes. Yes, it's me fucking heart.
I'm trying to tell you but you'll not listen.

01:56.480 --> 01:59.870
AMANDA: Mr Blake, if you continue
to speak to us like that

02:00.000 --> 02:02.798
that's not gonna be very helpful
for your assessment.

02:02.920 --> 02:05.388
If you could just answer
the question, please.

02:05.800 --> 02:07.199
DAN: Yes.
AMANDA: Okay.

02:11.440 --> 02:17.072
Do you ever experience any loss of control
leading to extensive evacuation of the bowel?

02:17.400 --> 02:19.072
DAN: No. But I cannot guarantee

02:19.080 --> 02:21.240
there won't be a first if we divvent
get to the point.

02:23.120 --> 02:26.112
AMANDA: Can you complete a simple
task of setting an alarm clock?

02:26.200 --> 02:28.395
DAN: (EXASPERATED) Oh, Jesus. Yes.

02:29.120 --> 02:32.317
Can I ask you a question?
Are you medically qualified?

02:33.080 --> 02:34.877
AMANDA: I'm a health care professional

02:35.000 --> 02:37.389
appointed by the
Department of Work and Pensions

02:37.520 --> 02:41.115
to carry out assessments for
Employment and Support Allowance.

02:41.360 --> 02:44.318
DAN: But there was a bloke out in the,
er, in the waiting room,

02:44.440 --> 02:46.670
he says that you work
for an American company.

02:46.800 --> 02:49.314
AMANDA: Our company's been
appointed by the Government.

02:49.760 --> 02:51.557
DAN: Are you a nurse?
Are you a doctor?

02:51.680 --> 02:53.432
AMANDA: I'm a health care professional.

02:55.120 --> 02:57.998
Listen, I've had a major heart attack.

02:58.120 --> 02:59.951
I nearly fell off the scaffolding.

03:01.120 --> 03:02.758
I wanna get back to work, too.

03:03.560 --> 03:05.869
Now, please, can we talk about me heart?

03:06.000 --> 03:08.594
Forget about me arse, that works a dream.

03:25.160 --> 03:26.912
(DOG BARKING DISTANTLY)

03:32.440 --> 03:33.839
(OBJECTS CLATTERING)

03:44.200 --> 03:45.599
(KEYS CHIMING)

03:47.160 --> 03:48.513
CHINA: Piper, you lazy bastard.

03:48.640 --> 03:50.676
Will you get out of bed
and do some housework!

03:51.880 --> 03:52.949
DAN: China!

03:53.200 --> 03:54.200
China!

03:54.600 --> 03:57.194
Sorry, Dan, just got a text
to go to work. I'm late.

03:57.200 --> 03:59.316
DAN: Did you enjoy your
chicken tikka masala?

03:59.680 --> 04:01.496
- CHINA: How did you know that?
- Cos I can bloody smell it.

04:01.520 --> 04:04.256
How many times have I told you about
leaving rubbish lying about the place,

04:04.280 --> 04:05.349
stinking it up?

04:05.480 --> 04:08.119
- Can I dump it later? I'm running late.
- No. Now!

04:08.200 --> 04:09.200
(SIGHS)

04:10.640 --> 04:12.039
Dan...

04:12.720 --> 04:14.472
Erm, I've got a big favour to ask

04:15.040 --> 04:17.507
I'm expecting a package. Really important.

04:18.079 --> 04:19.616
They've changed my hours, so I won't be in.

04:19.640 --> 04:21.240
Can you keep an eye out for the postman?

04:21.760 --> 04:24.433
If you swear nae more rubbish.

04:26.040 --> 04:28.554
- Catch! (LAUGHS)
- Don't you fucking dare.

04:29.160 --> 04:31.230
- I'll kick your arse into next week.
- Okay.

04:32.320 --> 04:34.231
DAN: Daft as a bloody brush.

04:42.840 --> 04:43.875
(BEEP)

04:45.480 --> 04:46.515
(BEEP)

04:48.640 --> 04:49.755
(BEEP)

04:50.120 --> 04:51.394
When can I go back to work?

04:51.760 --> 04:53.671
NURSE: Ah, not yet, that's for certain.

04:55.160 --> 04:56.275
You're making progress.

04:58.280 --> 05:02.831
I think if we just
continue you on the same dosage.

05:03.280 --> 05:05.271
And, yeah, rehab exercise.

05:05.640 --> 05:08.279
We'll see if we can
the pumping capacity to increase.

05:08.280 --> 05:09.679
- (MUMBLES) Yeah.
- And it might.

05:10.760 --> 05:14.673
But if not, we might need to look
at fitting you with a defibrillator.

05:16.000 --> 05:19.072
Keep up with the exercise, keep moving.
That's gonna build you up.

05:19.280 --> 05:20.918
But you need to be rested as well.

05:21.280 --> 05:23.032
Well, I'm a bit of a night owl, you know.

05:23.160 --> 05:25.276
I got into the habit
when I was looking after the missus

05:25.280 --> 05:26.679
