05:32.880 --> 05:34.996
How you doing, son? How you doing?

05:35.280 --> 05:37.077
- All right.
- How's the old ticker?

05:37.200 --> 05:38.838
Ah, you know, me marathon days are over.

05:38.960 --> 05:41.076
But, you know,
I'll be fine in a month or two.

05:41.200 --> 05:43.191
Ah, well, be leaving that Viagra alone.

05:43.320 --> 05:44.309
I'll keep it for you, shall I?

05:44.320 --> 05:46.788
- Aye, I probably need it more than you.
- (DAN LAUGHING)

05:49.920 --> 05:52.753
Right, well, owt you want here?

05:54.320 --> 05:56.993
- Have a look (LAUGHS)
- Oh, that's nice, aye.

05:57.480 --> 06:00.313
Meranti, aye, African Meranti.
It's great, man.

06:02.320 --> 06:04.320
So, er, d'you reckon
you'll get back to Ferguson's?

06:05.120 --> 06:06.336
Depends on the work, I suppose.

06:06.360 --> 06:08.430
I mean, you know what it's like.
It's up and down.

06:08.560 --> 06:09.595
Aye, well.

06:09.840 --> 06:11.990
- (MACHINE BUZZING)
- Gotta see this.

06:19.800 --> 06:20.915
There you go.

06:21.040 --> 06:22.996
Oh, that's a lovely piece.

06:24.800 --> 06:27.394
Aye, I'll have the...
I'll have the lads drop it by for you.

06:27.640 --> 06:30.438
Erm, are you all right?

06:31.200 --> 06:32.519
I'm on the mend.

06:32.920 --> 06:36.151
(STAMMERS) I mean, I can get your shopping
sorted out for you, you know.

06:36.280 --> 06:38.336
Like, the heavy stuff and that,
like, it's nae bother.

06:38.360 --> 06:41.079
(CHUCKLES) Thanks, Joe.
You know, I like to get out and about.

06:41.200 --> 06:42.349
Gives us something to do.

06:43.200 --> 06:44.920
Well, give us a shout if you need anything.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.797
I mean, I mean that.

06:47.360 --> 06:49.351
You, you gave us a big fright, you know.

