Oi! What are ye playing at?

09:16.320 --> 09:19.392
I knew it was ye! I knew it was ye
letting your dog shit round here.

09:19.520 --> 09:20.589
I'm walking me dog.

09:20.720 --> 09:23.871
DAN: I knew it was you bringing your dog
in here, shitting all over the place.

09:24.120 --> 09:26.918
MAN: Oh shut your mouth,
you stupid baldy bastard.

09:27.040 --> 09:31.238
Oi! Ye, if I come down there,
I'll rub your bloody face in it, man!

09:31.440 --> 09:33.510
DAN: Take it to your own place
and let it shit round there.

09:33.520 --> 09:35.816
- DAN: Go and get a bag and clean that up.
- Aye, I'm gonna get a bag

09:35.840 --> 09:36.976
I tell you what, ye talk shite!

09:37.000 --> 09:38.440
DAN: Here, look, you just get a bag!

09:38.520 --> 09:40.896
- Come back here and bloody clean that up.
- Oh, shut up, man, will you!

09:40.920 --> 09:43.559
Hey! I'll come and shite
in your garden, shall I?

09:43.560 --> 09:44.993
MAN: Shut up.

09:45.560 --> 09:46.560
Hello?

09:47.320 --> 09:50.392
(MUSIC PLAYING ON PHONE)

09:53.560 --> 09:55.096
AUTOMATED FEMALE:
Thank you for waiting.

09:55.120 --> 09:59.477
Please continue to hold and we will answer
your call as soon as possible.

09:59.800 --> 10:02.439
- (ON-HOLD MUSIC PLAYING)
- (SIGHS)

10:18.560 --> 10:20.994
Morning, mate.
Got a package for Mr Max Million.

10:21.560 --> 10:23.755
- "Mr Max Million"?
- POSTMAN: Yeah. Mr Max Million.

10:23.880 --> 10:25.074
My address?

10:25.600 --> 10:26.828
Yeah, definitely this address.

10:27.520 --> 10:29.636
- Where's it from?
- China.

10:29.960 --> 10:31.678
Oh. Give it here.

10:35.080 --> 10:36.593
D'you know how long
I've been on this phone?

10:36.600 --> 10:38.158
One hour, forty-eight minutes.

10:38.320 --> 10:41.437
Jesus Christ, that's longer than
a football match. It'll cost a fortune.

10:42.000 --> 10:44.200
MAN: (ON PHONE) I'm sorry, sir,
but it's been very busy.

10:44.440 --> 10:45.589
There must be some mistake.

10:45.680 --> 10:47.511
I've got a serious heart condition.

10:47.600 --> 10:50.239
I'm in rehab and the doctor's
told us I cannae go back to work.

10:50.520 --> 10:53.671
Now, I was getting the benefits
fine until that bloody assessment.

10:55.080 --> 10:57.176
MAN: (ON PHONE) I see you've only
scored twelve points, er,

10:57.200 --> 10:58.918
and you need 15 to obtain benefits.

10:59.040 --> 11:01.110
Oh, points, that's your game?

11:01.840 --> 11:04.056
MAN: (ON PHONE) I'm sorry, sir,
but according to our health, er,

11:04.080 --> 11:05.638
health care professional,

11:05.640 --> 11:07.073
you've been deemed fit for work.

11:08.200 --> 11:10.031
So she knows better than my doctor,

11:10.440 --> 11:12.829
a consultant surgeon and a physio team?

11:13.640 --> 11:15.631
Well, I wanna appeal.

11:15.720 --> 11:17.096
MAN: (ON PHONE) Well, that's fine,

11:17.120 --> 11:19.520
but you'll have to first request
a mandatory reconsideration.

11:20.280 --> 11:21.918
What the bloody hell does that mean?

11:22.280 --> 11:24.696
MAN: (ON PHONE) It means the decision
maker will reconsider it

11:24.720 --> 11:27.678
and if he comes to the same
decision, you can then appeal.

11:28.320 --> 11:29.880
Right, well put us down for that, then.

11:30.520 --> 11:32.016
MAN: (ON PHONE)
Okay, sir, but you must wait

11:32.040 --> 11:33.632
to get a call from the decision maker.

11:34.280 --> 11:35.315
Why?

11:36.160 --> 11:38.160
MAN: (ON PHONE)
To tell you what the decision is.

11:38.640 --> 11:40.517
But that's already been decided.

11:41.520 --> 11:43.954
MAN: (ON PHONE)
It is, but you're supposed to get the call,

11:44.080 --> 11:45.513
before the letter.

11:45.680 --> 11:47.318
Well, is he gonna change his mind?

11:47.680 --> 11:50.080
MAN: (ON PHONE) No, the call's
just to discuss the decision.

11:51.120 --> 11:53.896
Well, I know what the decision is,
I've got the letter here in front of us.

11:53.920 --> 11:55.672
D'you want us to read it to you?

11:56.560 --> 11:57.896
MAN: (ON PHONE)
But he should have called you first.

11:57.920 --> 11:59.194
But he didn't.

11:59.360 --> 12:01.296
- MAN: (ON PHONE) But he should have.
- (SIGHS IN DISGUST)

12:01.320 --> 12:03.656
Well unless we've got a time machine,
we're pretty much knackered,

12:03.680 --> 12:05.033
divvent you agree?

12:05.480 --> 12:06.696
MAN: (ON PHONE)
Er, he has to call you first, sir.

12:06.720 --> 12:08.358
(SIGHS) Listen,

12:09.600 --> 12:12.672
can you not just put him on now,
so I don't have to waste any more time?

12:13.280 --> 12:14.760
MAN: (ON PHONE) I can't do that, sir.

12:15.080 --> 12:16.479
Where is he?

12:16.680 --> 12:18.496
MAN: (ON PHONE)
He'll give you a call back when he, er,

12:18.520 --> 12:20.670
- he gets the chance.
- (SIGHS) When?

12:21.400 --> 12:22.992
MAN: (ON PHONE) I don't know, sir.

12:23.720 --> 12:26.109
(SIGHS) This is ridiculous, man.

12:28.560 --> 12:29.959
(BABY COOING)

12:45.160 --> 12:47.469
On the one hand, Jobseeker's Allowance,

12:47.600 --> 12:49.477
only for those able and ready to work.

12:49.600 --> 12:53.070
But if you're ill, you have to apply
for Employment and Support,

12:53.200 --> 12:55.200
- get an assessment carried out.
- (WOMAN COUGHING)

12:55.440 --> 12:57.431
Well, I've done that
but they've knocked us back.

12:57.720 --> 12:59.576
Right, well if you've
been deemed fit for work,

12:59.600 --> 13:01.716
your only option is Jobseeker's Allowance.

13:01.840 --> 13:03.920
Or proceed with the appeal on
Employment and Support.

13:04.360 --> 13:06.237
Well, can you give me a form for...

13:06.360 --> 13:07.800
You know, erm, Jobseeker's Allowance

13:07.920 --> 13:10.309
and then an appeal form
Employment and Support?

13:10.440 --> 13:11.839
You have to apply online, sir.

13:11.960 --> 13:14.030
(SIGHS) I cannot do that.

13:14.320 --> 13:16.601
Well that's how it is, sir.
Or you can phone the helpline.

13:16.640 --> 13:18.756
(SIGHS) Listen, you know,
you give me a plot of land,

13:18.760 --> 13:20.079
I can build you a house.

13:20.200 --> 13:22.759
But I've never been
anywhere near a computer.

13:22.760 --> 13:24.751
D'you know what, we're digital by default.

13:24.760 --> 13:26.034
Oh, here we gan.

13:26.200 --> 13:28.759
I hear this all the time on the phone,
"I'm digital by default."

13:28.760 --> 13:30.591
Well I'm pencil by default.

13:30.760 --> 13:33.479
Look, I mean, what happens
if you just cannae do it?

13:33.760 --> 13:36.957
There's a special number
if you've been diagnosed as dyslexic.

13:37.240 --> 13:40.630
Right, well can you give us that?
Cos with computers I'm dyslexic.

13:40.760 --> 13:43.797
You'll find it online, sir.
I must ask you to leave now,

13:43.880 --> 13:46.474
- if you've got no appointment.
- (DAN SIGHS)

13:50.200 --> 13:52.240
- (WOMAN COUGHING)
- MANAGER: Right, can I help you?

13:52.360 --> 13:55.511
Yeah, I'm here to see about
changing my work coach.

13:56.600 --> 13:58.955
- (DAN EXHALES)
- Thomas Armstrong, please.

14:01.080 --> 14:02.798
Hang on a minute, Thomas, hang on.

14:03.000 --> 14:05.309
Erm, would you like to take a seat?

14:05.440 --> 14:08.876
Oh, I just need a minute. I just felt...
I'm just feeling dizzy, you know.

14:09.000 --> 14:11.798
- Come and sit down.
- Oh, cheers, thanks.

14:12.880 --> 14:14.313
Could you move up, please, love?

14:14.440 --> 14:16.078
Thanks, pet, thank you.

14:16.200 --> 14:19.590
- All right. I'll just get you a glass of water.
- (SIGHS) Thank you.

14:28.400 --> 14:30.709
Oh, thank you, pet.
Thank you.

14:30.840 --> 14:32.637
Are you all right?
You look a bit pale.

14:32.840 --> 14:35.832
It's just so bloody confusing,
all the jargon.

14:36.280 --> 14:39.440
I mean, there must be some mistake.
I'm just ganning round and round in circles.

14:39.560 --> 14:41.296
KATIE: I've, I've really gotta
get this sorted out.

14:41.320 --> 14:42.816
SHEILA: Oh I can understand that,
but you were late.

14:42.840 --> 14:46.515
Thomas. You sit here
and drink your water, pet.

14:46.640 --> 14:47.834
Thank you.

14:50.240 --> 14:51.336
So now you're gonna sanction me so, er...

14:51.360 --> 14:53.828
- No, I'm not gonna sanction you.
- I may not get any money for a month.

14:53.840 --> 14:56.416
I'm gonna refer you to the decision maker
and they'll make the decision

14:56.440 --> 14:58.416
- on whether they're gonna sanction you.
- That's ridiculous...

14:58.440 --> 15:00.536
I'm not actually making the decision,
they're gonna do that.

15:00.560 --> 15:02.630
SHEILA: And then if they do decide
to sanction you,

15:02.760 --> 15:03.875
then you will take a 40%
cut in your benefits.

15:03.880 --> 15:06.016
KATIE: I know what it is,
I don't need you to explain it to me.

15:06.040 --> 15:07.856
- I'm more than aware...
- Well there isn't anything else

15:07.880 --> 15:08.869
anybody can do today.

15:08.880 --> 15:10.456
So what I'm gonna have to do is,
look, I think I'm...

15:10.480 --> 15:12.256
I've decided to...
Are you gonna put me in for a sanction?

15:12.280 --> 15:13.416
I have to, I have to follow the rules.

15:13.440 --> 15:15.016
And the thing is if you're gonna,
be aggressive with me

15:15.040 --> 15:17.696
- then I'm gonna have to ask you...
- It's not about me being aggressive.

15:17.720 --> 15:20.576
- I'm gonna have to ask you to leave.
- I'm trying to explain to you a situation

15:20.600 --> 15:21.635
and you don't care.

15:21.760 --> 15:24.696
- SHEILA: Er, security. Security?
- I don't know why people like you do this job.

15:24.720 --> 15:25.869
SHEILA: I'm referring you
to the decision maker.

15:25.880 --> 15:28.792
KATIE: It's all the same thing.
I don't wanna hear your language

15:28.880 --> 15:30.776
- SHEILA: I, I beg your pardon.
- Listen, I, I'm sorry, love,

15:30.800 --> 15:32.536
- but you're gonna have to leave.
- Yeah, all right, frankly,

15:32.560 --> 15:34.136
take your hands off me.
I'm gonna speak to the manager,

15:34.160 --> 15:36.776
- I don't wanna speak to you.
- The fact is I'm just trying to explain...

15:36.800 --> 15:37.936
- Sorry?
- I'm just explaining...

15:37.960 --> 15:39.136
Well it's not you I wanna speak to...

15:39.160 --> 15:40.976
- You can go back up there.
- Right, come and talk to me then

15:41.000 --> 15:42.776
- if you've got something to say.
- Okay. Sorry.

15:42.800 --> 15:43.915
All right.

15:43.920 --> 15:46.536
I've tried to explain to the woman,
